import itertools
plt.figure(figsize=(15,20))

col=['cement', 'slag', 'ash', 'water', 'superplastic', 'coarseagg',
       'fineagg', 'age']
for i,j in itertools.zip_longest(col,range(len(col))):
    print(i,j)
    plt.subplot(4,2,j+1)
    ax = sns.distplot(df[i],color='green',rug=True)
    plt.axvline(df[i].mean(),linestyle="dashed",label="mean", color='black')
    plt.axvline(df[i].median(),linestyle="dashed",label="median", color='red')
    plt.axvline(df[i].std(),linestyle="dashed",label="std", color='blue')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title(i)
    plt.xlabel("")

from sklearn.model_selection import KFold,cross_val_score

kfold= KFold(n_splits=10, random_state=7)

LinearRegression¶

In [45]:
lineaR=LinearRegression()

lineaR.fit(X_train, y_train)

print('Coefficent:',lineaR.coef_)

trainingScore=lineaR.score(X_train,y_train)
testingScore=lineaR.score(X_test,y_test)
y_predicted = lineaR.predict(X_test)

#print('Training Score',trainingScore)

RMSE=np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_predicted))
MSE = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_predicted)
MAE = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_predicted)
R2Score = r2_score(y_test, y_predicted)
Linear_CV=cross_val_score(lineaR, X_test, y_test, cv=kfold,scoring='neg_mean_squared_error').ravel()


# modeling.append('Linear Regression')
# scores.append(linear_score)
# TRS.append(trainingScore)

MLA=lineaR.__class__.__name__

#compare_model = pd.DataFrame({'Model': 'Linear','scores': scores,'Training Score': TRS})
linear_model=pd.DataFrame([[MLA, trainingScore,testingScore,RMSE,MSE,MAE,R2Score, Linear_CV.mean(),Linear_CV.std(),Linear_CV.min(),Linear_CV.max()]],
                          columns=['Model','Training Score','Testing Score','RMSE','MSE','MAE','R2Score','CV_Mean','CV_std','CV_min','CV_max'])
#    return pd.DataFrame([[MLA, trainR2Score, testR2Score]],columns=['MLA','trainR2Score','testR2Score'])

PolyNomial Regression - Degree 2:¶
In [49]:
poly2=PolynomialFeatures(degree=2, interaction_only=True)

X_polytrain2=poly2.fit_transform(X_train)
X_polytest2=poly2.fit_transform(X_test)

print('X_polytrain2',X_polytrain2.shape)

lineaR.fit(X_polytrain2, y_train)

trainingScore=lineaR.score(X_polytrain2,y_train)
testingScore=lineaR.score(X_polytest2,y_test)
y_predicted2 = lineaR.predict(X_polytest2)

#print('Training Score',trainingScore)

RMSE=np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_predicted2))
MSE = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_predicted2)
MAE = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_predicted2)
R2Score = r2_score(y_test, y_predicted2)
poly2_CV=cross_val_score(lineaR, X_polytrain2, y_train.values.ravel(), cv=kfold,scoring='neg_mean_squared_error').mean()



Poly2Model=pd.DataFrame([['PolyNomialDegree2', trainingScore,testingScore,RMSE,MSE,MAE,R2Score, poly2_CV.mean(),poly2_CV.std(),poly2_CV.min(),poly2_CV.max()]],
                          columns=['Model','Training Score','Testing Score','RMSE','MSE','MAE','R2Score','CV_Mean','CV_std','CV_min','CV_max'])

Ridge¶

In [53]:
Ridge=Ridge(alpha=0.3)

Ridge.fit(X_train, y_train)

print('Coefficent:',Ridge.coef_)

trainingScore=Ridge.score(X_train,y_train)
testingScore=Ridge.score(X_test,y_test)
y_predictedRidge = Ridge.predict(X_test)

#print('Training Score',trainingScore)

RMSE=np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_predictedRidge))
MSE = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_predictedRidge)
MAE = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_predictedRidge)
R2Score = r2_score(y_test, y_predictedRidge)
Ridge_CV=cross_val_score(Ridge, X_test, y_test, cv=kfold,scoring='neg_mean_squared_error').ravel()


# modeling.append('Linear Regression')
# scores.append(linear_score)
# TRS.append(trainingScore)
